Feature: GitHub issues auto-enter the backlog root and the swarm notices undrained intakes

  # BL-558 — infrastructure adapters only. Specifier drains; coordinator promotes.
  # Complements BL-114 (issue loop closing) and the existing label-triggered
  # swarm-intake.yml workflow. Does NOT assign GitHub scanning to the coordinator LLM.

  # ── Slice 1: scheduled GitHub auto-intake ──────────────────────────────────

  # BL-558 scan-01
  Scenario: an open issue without a backlog file is intaked on the next scan
    Given an open GitHub issue with number N and no swarm-intake label
    And no file matching backlog/GH-N-*.yaml exists on main
    When the scheduled auto-intake workflow runs
    Then a file backlog/GH-N-<slug>.yaml is committed on main
    And the file's id is GH-N and source is the issue URL
    And the issue receives a queued-for-swarm comment naming that path
    And the issue is labeled swarm-intake

  # BL-558 scan-02
  Scenario: an issue that already has a GH-N backlog file is skipped
    Given an open GitHub issue with number N
    And backlog/GH-N-existing.yaml already exists on main
    When the scheduled auto-intake workflow runs
    Then no second GH-N file is created
    And the workflow exits successfully

  # BL-558 scan-03
  Scenario: an issue already labeled swarm-specced is not re-intaked
    Given a closed or open issue with label swarm-specced
    When the scheduled auto-intake workflow runs
    Then no new backlog/GH-<n>-*.yaml is created for that issue

  # BL-558 scan-04
  Scenario: parallel intakes both land on main
    Given two distinct open issues N and M without backlog files
    When two auto-intake workflow runs commit in parallel
    Then both backlog/GH-N-*.yaml and backlog/GH-M-*.yaml exist on main
    And neither workflow fails its push step

  # BL-558 scan-05
  Scenario: the manual label-triggered intake path still works
    Given the existing swarm-intake.yml label workflow
    When a human adds the swarm-intake label to an issue
    Then the same GH-N yaml shape is written as the scheduled scan

  # ── Slice 2: handoffd root-intake nudge ────────────────────────────────────

  # BL-558 nudge-01
  Scenario: undrained GH yaml at backlog root triggers a coordinator nudge
    Given backlog/GH-22-example.yaml exists at the backlog root
    And no root-intake nudge note is pending for the coordinator
    And the root-intake nudge cooldown has elapsed
    When the handoffd root-intake nudge sweep runs
    Then a note is delivered to the coordinator
    And the note's message includes a fixed root-intake nudge phrase

  # BL-558 nudge-02
  Scenario: no nudge when backlog root has no intake yaml
    Given backlog root has no GH- INTAKE- or BL- yaml files
    When the handoffd root-intake nudge sweep runs
    Then no root-intake nudge is sent

  # BL-558 nudge-03
  Scenario: pending root-intake nudge is not duplicated
    Given a coordinator inbox already contains the root-intake nudge phrase
    When the handoffd root-intake nudge sweep runs
    Then no additional root-intake nudge is sent

  # BL-558 nudge-04
  Scenario: root-intake nudge respects cooldown
    Given a root-intake nudge was sent recently within the cooldown window
    And no pending root-intake nudge remains
    When the handoffd root-intake nudge sweep runs
    Then no new root-intake nudge is sent

  # BL-558 nudge-05
  Scenario: the daemon never drains or promotes from a root-intake nudge
    Given the root-intake nudge sweep fires
    When its side effects are inspected
    Then no file is moved from backlog root to paused or active
    And no git commit is made by the daemon

  # ── Slice 3: second-swarm wake on backlog root ─────────────────────────────

  # BL-558 wake-01
  Scenario: a push that only adds backlog/GH-N-slug.yaml wakes the primary swarm
    Given a push to main that adds backlog/GH-99-new-intake.yaml
    When the second-swarm wake-up workflow evaluates changed paths
    Then the primary swarm is eligible for a remote wake nudge
    And a push that only touches backlog/active or backlog/paused behavior is unchanged

  # ── Slice 4: pipeline board lists YAML root intakes ────────────────────────

  # BL-558 board-01
  Scenario: ROOT INTAKE includes a GH yaml at backlog root
    Given backlog/GH-23-console-mini-app.yaml at the backlog root with title in yaml
    When the pipeline board root-intake list is built
    Then an entry with id GH-23 appears in the ROOT INTAKE section

  # BL-558 board-02
  Scenario: ROOT INTAKE still includes markdown intakes
    Given backlog/INTAKE-20260722-example.md at the backlog root
    When the pipeline board root-intake list is built
    Then that markdown intake still appears unchanged

# Non-behavioral gates:
#  - Slice 1 workflow: no ${{ }} inside run: bodies (BL-227 posture); secrets from
#    GITHUB_TOKEN only; slug/title/body env-routed.
#  - Slice 1 push: git pull --rebase (or equivalent retry) before push; same bot identity
#    as swarm-intake.yml.
#  - Slice 2 pure decision functions live in chase_sweep_lib.bb with tests in
#    dispatch_gap_test_runner.bb (mirror open-slot-nudge tests).
#  - Slice 2 nudge target: coordinator on mono-router packs; specifier on multi-role
#    swarms — document the branch in handoffd or chase_sweep_lib.
#  - Slice 3: extend remote_wakeup_lib / workflow path filters; unit-test path classification.
#  - Slice 4: readRootIntakeFiles in telegram-front-desk-bot.ts; exclude README.md/STEERING.md.
#  - Coordinator and specifier prompts: no new GitHub polling instructions; optional one-line
#    cross-reference that daemon root-intake nudges exist (do not duplicate mono-router text).
#  - BL-114 issue_specced.sh / issue_done.sh unchanged.
